  "prompt": "Where did the name Twitter come from?",
  "response": "The name \"Twitter\" was chosen by the co-founders of the social media platform after brainstorming and searching through a dictionary for words that captured the essence of their concept. They were looking for a word that conveyed the idea of a short burst of inconsequential information, something not too heavy, that would encapsulate the nature of their service: to allow users to post brief messages. They landed on \"Twitter,\" which fit perfectly as it means a series of short, high-pitched sounds, akin to birds chirping, which also conveys the idea of light, casual communication.",
